<h1>About Transportation Tracker</h1>

<p>
  The <strong>Transportation Tracker</strong> project integrates multiple datasets to provide detailed 
  information on cities, bus routes, and stops. This project is built using Rails and PostgreSQL, 
  and it includes real-world transit data as well as synthetic test data.
</p>

<h2>Data Sources Used</h2>
<p>The project utilizes <strong>three main data sources</strong>:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Faker-Generated Dataset</strong> (Randomized Fake Data)</li>
  <li><strong>GTFS CSV Data</strong> (Downloaded from <a href="https://transitfeeds.com/" target="_blank">TransitFeeds.com</a>)</li>
  <li><strong>Manually Added Data</strong> (Custom Cities, Bus Routes, and Stops)</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h3>Faker-Generated Dataset</h3>
<p>
  This dataset is generated using the Faker gem in <code>db/seeds.rb</code>. It provides random but realistic city, 
  route, and stop data for development and testing purposes.
</p>

<strong>Data Structure:</strong>
<ul>
  <li><strong>City:</strong> Name, State, Country</li>
  <li><strong>BusRoute:</strong> Name, Route Number, City ID</li>
  <li><strong>Stop:</strong> Name, Latitude, Longitude</li>
</ul>

<strong>Example Faker Data:</strong>
<ul>
  <li><strong>City:</strong> "Port Rudolf", "Beahaven ", "Patsyhaven"</li>
  <li><strong>Bus Route:</strong> "597 Alta Radial", "Martin Neck"</li>
  <li><strong>Stop:</strong> "E Genesee St & Town Hall Rd", "S Midler Ave & Glencove Rd"</li>
</ul>

<strong>Purpose:</strong> Provides dummy data for development and testing.

<hr>

<h3>GTFS CSV Data (Real-World Transit Data)</h3>
<p>
  The <strong>General Transit Feed Specification (GTFS)</strong> dataset was downloaded from 
  <a href="https://transitfeeds.com/" target="_blank">TransitFeeds.com</a> and includes real transit stop data.
</p>

<strong>Data Structure:</strong>
<ul>
  <li><strong>stop_id:</strong> Unique ID of the stop</li>
  <li><strong>stop_name:</strong> Stop name (e.g., "Union Station")</li>
  <li><strong>stop_lat:</strong> Latitude (e.g., 43.645)</li>
  <li><strong>stop_lon:</strong> Longitude (e.g., -79.3807)</li>
</ul>

<strong>Example from <code>stops.csv</code>:</strong>
<pre>
stop_id,stop_name,stop_lat,stop_lon
1001,Union Station,43.645,-79.3807
1002,Main Street,43.70011,-79.4163
</pre>

<strong>Purpose:</strong> Enhances accuracy by using real-world transit data.

<hr>

<h3>Manually Added Data</h3>
<p>
  Additional data, such as specific bus routes, stops, and agencies, were manually created to complement Faker and GTFS data.
</p>

<strong>Example of Manually Added Data:</strong>
<ul>
  <li><strong>City:</strong> "Kent"</li>
  <li><strong>Bus Route:</strong> "Downtown Loop" (Route #101)</li>
  <li><strong>Stop:</strong> "King & Bay"</li>
</ul>

<strong>Purpose:</strong> Complements Faker and GTFS data with controlled test data.

